Comment: This is a game that i played with a player that had less points than me...Also i don't like d4 for opening but that happened unfortunately so i had to fight for the game...I have won in the past as black games that started with d4, but it's an opening a don't like that much......
d5 as a reply...
c4 then...
And i'm taking the pawn..
Then i expected him play Nc3 but he played e4 instead..
i replied e5...
Then he played d5 and he built a strong centre...
Now i'm developing my pieces...
And he's pushing me with his bishop...
h6 is typical...
He took it then...
And i'm taking the bishop with my queen...Also a good position for my queen though i still didn't finish the development...
He's taking the pawn and equalize...
i'm trying to push the f2 pawn...
A bad movement i think as he's blocking his knight....
Now i think i'm fine with the my piece's development and i'm pushing f2 and f3 squares as well...At least it's a phenomenal pressure...
h3 is a logical reply... But the king's side is quite disorganized...
Still his pawns are staying strong in the centre and i'm moving back the bishop..
He's developing the knight but the king's side setting is feeling awkard and the g2 square is weak and unprotected...
So my target is the g2 pawn...
